          "scid": "an10.267-746:1.0.2",
          "en": "The Book of the Tens"
        },
        {
          "scid": "an10.267-746:1.0.3",
          "en": "267–746."
        },
        {
          "scid": "an10.267-746:1.1.4",
          "en": "“Bhikkhus, for direct knowledge … for full understanding … for the utter destruction … for the abandoning … for the destruction … for the vanishing … for the fading away … for the cessation … for the giving up … for the relinquishment of hatred … of delusion … of anger … of hostility … of denigration … of insolence … of envy … of miserliness … of deceitfulness … of craftiness … of obstinacy … of vehemence … of conceit … of arrogance … of intoxication … of heedlessness … these ten things are to be developed.”"
        },
        {
          "scid": "an10.267-746:1.2.5",
          "en": "This is what the Blessed One said. Elated, those bhikkhus delighted in the Blessed One’s statement."
        },
        {
          "scid": "an10.267-746:1.2.6",
          "en": "The Book of the Tens is finished."
        }
      ],
